This is a simple example about how to write C++ extention for Python via SIP. Most of the example is from 

http://www.riverbankcomputing.co.uk/static/Docs/sip4/using.html

Steps to test:

g++ -o word.o -c word.cpp
ar rcs libword.a word.o
cp libword.a /usr/local/lib
g++ -o foo main.cpp -lword
./foo
sip -c . word.sip
python configure.py
make
make install
open python, and run:

rom word import Word
a = 'Casablanca.1942'
print 'reverse', a
b = Word(a)
print 'to', b.reverse()
